    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="section-num">03 — THE DIFFERENCE</span>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 36px);">Same agent. Same prompt.<br>Completely different output.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="compare-list" style="margin-top: -16px;">

      <!-- Scenario 1 -->
      <div class="compare-row">
        <div class="compare-scenario-label">Scenario: Daily standup prep</div>
        <div class="compare-cell">
          <div class="compare-cell-tag">
            <svg width="8" height="8" viewBox="0 0 8 8"><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="4" fill="#333"/></svg>
            Without ToggleX
          </div>
          <div class="compare-prompt"><span class="prompt-arrow">›</span> "What did I get done yesterday?"</div>
          <div class="compare-response">I'm not sure — I don't have access to your work history. Can you walk me through what you remember doing, and I can help you organize it into a standup update?</div>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-cell is-after">
          <div class="compare-cell-tag">
            <svg width="8" height="8" viewBox="0 0 8 8"><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="4" fill="#00FFB2"/></svg>
            With ToggleX
          </div>
          <div class="compare-prompt"><span class="prompt-arrow">›</span> "What did I get done yesterday?"</div>
          <div class="compare-response">Yesterday you had 3 deep work sessions (4.8h total). You shipped the tick-size normalization branch, reviewed 2 PRs on the dashboard repo, updated the sprint backlog in Notion, and spent 45min in Figma on the settings page redesign. Want me to format that as a standup update?</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Scenario 2 -->
      <div class="compare-row">
        <div class="compare-scenario-label">Scenario: Priority management</div>
        <div class="compare-cell">
          <div class="compare-cell-tag">
            <svg width="8" height="8" viewBox="0 0 8 8"><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="4" fill="#333"/></svg>
            Without ToggleX
          </div>
          <div class="compare-prompt"><span class="prompt-arrow">›</span> "What should I focus on today?"</div>
          <div class="compare-response">That depends on your priorities and deadlines. What projects are you currently working on? What's most urgent? I can help you prioritize once I know your current workload.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-cell is-after">
          <div class="compare-cell-tag">
